        "description": "QR Code Link to This Post This apartment is available for rent immediately. The apartment is located in Malden, MA. The apartment is very spacious with nearly 1,600 square feet of space. The apartment is two floors and has been used both as a 3 bedroom unit or 4 bedroom unit. The apartment includes a large living room, kitchen, and one full bathroom with tall ceilings. The unit has a mini split for heating and cooling of the first floor in a space that was a porch that has been gut renovated with new insulation, sheetrock, painting and lighting and has been used as either a fourth bedroom or bonus space. The primary bedroom on the first floor has amble closet space boasting two separate closet areas. One of the closet areas is essentially a second room that has been used as an office. On the second floor are the other two bedrooms. There is free laundry access in the basement of the building. The kitchen is quite large and allows for ample storage. Additionally, there is a gas grill on the property in the backyard. There is a nice backyard with a patio area and patio furniture available. Before the backyard is the driveway which comes with a parking spot. The backyard abuts Malden’s bike path, which is a wonderful area to walk and bike. The path runs from Revere up to downtown Malden where the Malden stop on the orange line is. Downtown Malden includes several fantastic bars and restaurants including Mystic Station, Faces Brewery, All Seasons Table, Exchange Street Bistro and many more. Downtown Malden also features a convenient orange line train stop second from the end, so it is less busy in the morning than stops closer to Boston yet is only 8 stops from the heart of downtown Boston (about 20 minutes on the train). The apartment is near downtown Malden and the orange line train stop with less than a mile walk and a convenient bus stop just 500 feet from the apartment. The apartment is also a quick 12 minute drive to the Encore Casino in Everett and 9 minute drive to Revere Beach.",
