        "ver": "Apartment",
        "info": "QR Code Link to This Post he Bartlett Atkinson historic 1805 brick Federalist mansion built by a renowned nineteenth century local shipbuilder offers for rent a spacious and exquisite 2-room studio apartment. This elegant in town, well maintained 6 unit property in downtown Newburyport includes HEAT and HOT WATER, an ASSIGNED PARKING SPACE, ORIGINAL FIREPLACE, WASHER/DRYER AND STORAGE. As you enter the mansion you encounter the prominent and impressive foyer with a grand suspended staircase. The spacious, elegant front living room of the apartment features period architecture with Indian shutters, intricate crown and dental molding, wainscoting and wide pine wood floors. Large windows with window seats provide an abundance of warm and natural light throughout the space. A separate galley kitchen has an adjacent eating area for a 2 seater table. The newly remolded bathroom (not yet photographed) is full size with bathtub and shower. This extraordinary downtown property is quiet and private with excellent tenants and perfectly blends historic character with the conveniences of modern seaside living that honors its 19th-century roots. Newburyport is renowned for its boutique and artisan’s shops, diverse and outstanding culinary restaurants, vibrant pubs and its historic waterfront and boardwalk along a sprawing designed park conceived by leading urbanist to serve as the city's green heartbeat. For outdoor enthusiasts enjoy miles of scenic rail trails for hiking and biking throughout the city and beyond, explore the beauty of hundreds of wooded acres of our prized Maudslay State Park through forests and meadows along the great Merrimac River, and visit the pristine sandy beaches of Plum Island—just a few miles. A maritime lovers experience awaits at your footsteps with boating, kayaking, paddle boarding rentals, fishing trips, whale watch excursions and sailing lessons. For Boston commuters and day trippers you are walking distance to commuter trains to North Station and to routes 1 and Interstate 95. Choose this prime Newburyport location for a quality lifestyle in its thriving and charming seaside city. Everything you need is at your doorstep! $2195 per month includes heat, hot water, parking and several attractive amenities. Available August 1. No dogs please. Non smokers thank you.",
