      "house_ger": {
        "id": "c3135d79-5f48-4409-b3f8-ae64bb68db9c",
        "name": "4 Rooms in JP House for Rent (1 Year Lease)",
        "location": "MA",
        "mainpic": "f50791f4-8e61-41b1-914a-8ef700dee466",
        "msg": "QR Code Link to This Post Hello everyone, We are a group of roommates looking to fill 3 (possibly 4) rooms in our 8-bedroom JP house with a move in date of September 1st. About the house: This is an older Victorian home with an excellent location. We’re a ~6 minute walk from the Stony Brook stop on the Orange line and only 15 minutes walk from Whole Foods, Stop and Shop, and lots of businesses/restaurants along Centre Street. The home is old and has some of the typical old home problems (floors are a little unlevel and such), and is awaiting some clean-ups/repairs, but we have a full kitchen (brand new stove), free washer/dryer in the basement (washer is brand new), and a lovely shared porch with a front yard (a couple of us have a small garden/plant oasis on the porch). There is ample street parking with a JP resident permit. The common space is huge with lots of windows. Zach is the only housemate on the first floor and he’s pretty quiet so it's a nice space to hang out or do work or hobbies. About the rooms (Letters Correspond to Photos) [AVAILABLE] Room A: $620/month - 2nd Floor - Small - Includes wooden bunk, but if you don’t like it we're happy to help you take it apart - Former tenant is willing to leave the ac installed [AVAILABLE] Room B: $855 - 2nd Floor - Fairly large room w/ multiple windows - Two Walk-in Closets - Recliner included, if desired (left behind by previous tenant) [AVAILABLE] Room D: $1,025 - 2nd Floor - Fairly large room w/ bay window - Walk-in Closet - The current tenant is offering to leave the Window AC installed. [Tentatively Opening] Room F: $775/month - 3rd Floor - Slanted Ceiling, single window - No closet in the room, but you will have exclusive use of the 3rd floor hallway closet. - Includes the Alcove where the chairs are pictured just outside of the room. About the current roommates: There are a lot of people in the house and we all have very different schedules/habits, currently we have 5 people staying on (Zachary, Alexandra, Brianne, L., and Réka) We all fit the description of young professionals/students. The house is surprisingly quiet for so many people. We're not big on wild parties and everyone is respectful of space/time etc. We have three full bathrooms and a communal kitchen/living room. About what we're looking for: This is a queer and trans friendly house so you must be okay with that. We're looking for respectful roommates who keep common areas clean and communicate well - we use a chore chart to manage communal tasks and bills are each hosted by a different roommate (ie, one hosts the electric, one the gas, and one the internet). Must be okay using Venmo for bills. No cats or dogs. About the process: Please introduce yourself, share your pronouns, and tell us a bit about yourself and what you’re looking for! We will collectively decide on new roommates and there will be at least one interview with one of the housemates. Anyone we decide on will be put in contact with the property manager Jonny. He requires a $25 fee for a credit check. Move - in cost will be first month, last month, and 3/4 month security. Please feel free to email with questions!",
