ary, Alexandra, Brianne, L., and Réka) We all fit the description of young professionals/students. The house is surprisingly quiet for so many people. We're not big on wild parties and everyone is respectful of space/time etc. We have three full bathrooms and a communal kitchen/living room. About what we're looking for: This is a queer and trans friendly house so you must be okay with that. We're looking for respectful roommates who keep common areas clean and communicate well - we use a chore chart to manage communal tasks and bills are each hosted by a different roommate (ie, one hosts the electric, one the gas, and one the internet). Must be okay using Venmo for bills. No cats or dogs. About the process: Please introduce yourself, share your pronouns, and tell us a bit about yourself and what you’re looking for! We will collectively decide on new roommates and there will be at least one interview with one of the housemates. Anyone we decide on will be put in contact with the property manager Jonny. He requires a $25 fee for a credit check. Move - in cost will be first month, last month, and 3/4 month security. Please feel free to email with questions!",
